# Privacy Policy for Tonepitch

Last updated: April 1, 2025

## Introduction

Tonepitch ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application (the "App").

## Information We Collect

### Information You Provide
- We do not collect any personal information from you.
- The App does not require any user accounts or registration.

### Information Automatically Collected
- The App requires microphone access to function as a guitar tuner.
- We do not store or transmit any audio data.
- We do not track your usage or collect analytics.

## How We Use Your Information
- We only use the microphone to analyze pitch in real-time for tuning purposes.
- We do not store or share any of your information with third parties.

## Data Security
- We do not store any data, so there is no risk of data breaches.
- All audio processing is done locally on your device.

## Children's Privacy
- The App is suitable for all ages.
- We do not knowingly collect any personal information from children.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy
- We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
- We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

## Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
tonepitch1@gmail.com

## California Privacy Rights
- We do not sell or share your personal information.
- We do not track your activity across other websites.

## European Union Privacy Rights
- We do not collect or process any personal data as defined under GDPR.
- We do not transfer any data outside the European Union. 
